                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>
                          Layman’s Prayer, in Amharic, <foreign xml:lang="am">አዳምን፡</foreign>, or <foreign xml:lang="am">ኖኅን፡</foreign> with incipip
                          <foreign xml:lang="am">
                            ኦ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ወአምላኪየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አዳምን፡ ከሲኦል፡ ያወጻሕ፡ እኔንም፡ ከሲኦል፡ አስጻኝ።...
                          </foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)"/>", top: on the meaning of Maccabees, <foreign xml:lang="am">መቃብያን፡ ማለት፡ ዓቃብያነ፡ ሕገ፡ ኦሪት፡ ማለት፡ ነው። ፲፫ናቸው።</foreign>, “Maccabees means keepers of the Law and they are thirteen.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)"/>", middle: Saying: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነቀዙ፡ ለነዋይ፡ ብእሲት፡ ወውሉድ፡ እሙንቱ።</foreign>, “The weevil of wealth is wife and children.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)"/>", in purple ink: note of birthday</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#66r"/> a small cross in the margin marks the midpoint of the psalms</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#153v"/>: Note: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈጸመ፡ ሰርዲስ፡ ሰርዲስሪን። ዘውእቱ፡ ስባሔ፡ ስባሔያት።</foreign>, “Here ends Särdis Särdisrin, which is Praise of Praises.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#177r"/>, col. 2, in purple ink: Concluding prayer for Psalter</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <desc>
                          Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#xiiir(ecto) #18r #19r #20r #50v"/>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#64v #68v"/>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#xiiiv(erso) #118v #138r #151"/>, etc.);
                          text has been removed (<locus target="#54r #63rv"/>, etc.)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                          the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                          lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#6r #10v #27r #28r"/>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">
